Amazing how QB retains her unique touch while also bringing in a very distinct sound of the original singer too... you can hear a bit of Reshma in her Reshma songs, and a you can clearly hear a touch of Musarrat Nazir in this one.... and yet, its all QB. 

QB and Masooma Anwar - voices to relish in the coming years....

snippet.textDisplay:
Ooooooo....I like that KIYUN? KIYUN? KIYUN? KIYUN? KIYUN? KIYUN? KIYUN?:-))))))))).....That "Kiyun bit" was Fucking Sexy....The people who are saying that they shouldn't have mixed the two songs....i somehow agree with that....but oh well you can record the 2 songs separately as 2 songs are long enough to be considered as separate songs...!!!!
Ok i will take my words back....Wot i have observed is that when you listen to this song "without the video" then you feel that they have blended the songs very well and its the best fusion you will ever get to hear. But "with the video" you feel like the two songs should have been sung separately in 2 different videos of coke studio. Kitni ajeeb baat hai ke video ke saath sun-nay say different feel hota hai aur video ke bagair sun-nay say different feel hota hai. I think video daikh kar insaan distract ho jaata hai...shaayad yehi wajha hai.....!!!!
